or &s;ufficiently con|&s;idered.</NOTE>.</L></Q>
<P>If any thing engages our attention in this pa&s;&s;age, it is the wildne&s;s of the fiction; in which however the poet had no &s;hare.</P>
<P>I will here add Arthur's intrigue with Ygerne.</P>
