We find it in Froi&s;&s;art, tom. iv. c. 87. And in other antient French writers. In the old Norman poem on the &s;ubject of king Dermod's expul&s;ion from his kingdom of Ireland, in the Lambeth library, it &s;eems more properly to &s;ignify, in a limited &s;en&s;e, the <HI>king's dome&s;tic</HI> SECRETARY.
<Q><L>Par &s;on <HI>demein<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI> LATINIER</L>
