See lord Lyttelton's Hi&s;t. Hen ii. vol. iv. App. p. 270. We might here render it literally his <HI>Latini&s;t,</HI> an officer retained by the king to draw up the public in&s;truments in Latin. As in DOMESDAI-BOOK. <Q REND="inline">"God|winus accipitrarius, Hugo LATINA|RIUS, Milo portarius."</Q> MS. Ex|cerpt. penes me. But in both the la&s;t in|&s;tances the word may bear its more general and exten&s;ive &s;ignification. Camden ex|plains LATIMER by <HI>interpreter.</HI> Rem. p. 158. See al&s;o p. 151. edit. 1674.</NOTE> latimer.</L>
