<P>Another of the&s;e fragments, evidently of the &s;ame com|po&s;ition, &s;eems to have been an introduction to the whole. It begins with the martyrdom of &s;aint Alban, and pa&s;&s;es on to the introduction of Wa&s;&s;ail, and to the names and divi&s;ion of England.</P>
