<P>I am not indeed quite certain, whether or no in &s;ome of the&s;e in&s;tances, Robert de Brunne may not mean his French original Peter Langtoft. But in the following lines he ma|ni<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter">e&s;tly refers to our romance of RICHARD, between which and Langtoft's chronicle he expre&s;&s;ly makes a di&s;tinction. And in the conclu&s;ion of the reign,</P>
<Q><PB N="121" REF="286">
<L>I knowe no more to ryme of dedes of kyng Richard:</L>
