<P>The romance of the SQUIRE OF LOW DEGREE, who loved the king's daughter of Hungary <NOTE N="s" PLACE="foot">It contains thirty-eight pages in quarto. <Q REND="inline">"Imprinted at London by me Wyllyam Copland."</Q> I have never &s;een it in ma|nu&s;cript.</NOTE>, is alluded to by Chaucer <HI>in the Rime of Sir Topas</HI> <NOTE N="t" PLACE="foot">See Ob&s;ervations on the Fairy Queen, i. &sect;. iv. p. 139.</NOTE>. The prince&s;s is thus repre&s;ented in her clo&s;et, adorned with painted gla&s;s, li&s;tening to the &s;quire's complaint <NOTE N="u" PLACE="foot">Sign. a. iii.</NOTE>.</P>
<Q><L>That ladi herde hys mournyng alle,</L>
