<L>Of holi men maken fe&s;te</L>
<L>Both day and nigth,</L>
<L>For to have the joye in hevene</L>
<L>(With aungells &s;ong, and merry &s;tevene,)</L>
<L>The which is brode and brigth:</L>
<L>To you all heige and lowe</L>
<L>The rigth &s;othe to biknowe</L>
<L>&YOGH;our &s;oules for to &s;ave, &amp;c <NOTE N="f" PLACE="foot">MS. ut &s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter">pr. f. 22.&mdash;72. b.</NOTE>.</L></Q>
<P>Our author's SCRIPTURE HISTORIES want the beginning. Here they begin with Jo&s;eph, and end with Daniel.</P>
<Q><PB N="219" REF="384">
<L>Ffor thritti pens<NOTE N="g" PLACE="foot">Thirty pence</NOTE> thei &s;old that childe</L>
